The hasAttr method checks if any of the matched elements have the specified attribute, which is a direct prerequisite for the eachAttr method to ensure that the attribute is present before attempting to retrieve its values.
The attr method returns a single attribute value, which can be used to construct assertions for the eachAttr method that returns a list of attribute values.
